<br>
Zak <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ulenardo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lenardo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1946<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/22/01 6:27:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bladesrevenge.mudservices.com/Lenardo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Figure 8 Question</span><hr size=1> ITs all in TIMING.<br>
<br>
figure eight will only be accessable to go off successfully AFTER an EVADE, and before the spawns next attack.<br>
<br>
if the spawn attacks again before your figure 8 goes off, it fails 100% of the time, even on a miss.<br>
<br>
this is how I do it.<br>
<br>
hotkey 1 - defenders fury<br>
hotkey 2 - figure 8<br>
hotkey 3 - friar's ally<br>
<br>
then i attack with defenders fury lead off.<br>
<br>
then i time the attack of the SPAWN and press the style button AFTER i get hit  by the spawn, thus i always get the style off -provided i hit the right button <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
if you mess up, wait an attack round or two to get the timing right again.<br>
<br>
doing it this way, provided i hit the right hotkey, and the figure 8 hits, i always get a friar's ally off - usually once or twice a fight.<br>
<br>
though defenders fury rocks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uzadkiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zadkiel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1747<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/22/01 6:43:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/dsantos/babykick.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Figure 8 Question</span><hr size=1> Yep, use a low delay weapon, and always wait until after the mob hits you to trigger your next style. So you can react to an evade or whatever.<br>
